RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAD DOG N JOE led the field inside through the first turn, improved his advantage running down the backstretch, continued unchallenged on the final turn and cruised home down the lane to win comfortably. JMR PURE SENSATION settled in midfield on the fence at the half, was on hold inside through the far turn, angled four wide turning for home, found his best stride late and burst between foes late to capture the runner up finish. FORESTERS PRINCESS stalked five wide in the early going, travelled in midfield four deep at the half, rallied three wide with three furlongs remaining and stayed on well to capture third money. COPINSAY had a good position on the rail tracking the leaders down the backside, advanced mildly inside on the final turn, was looking for room in upper stretch, shifted inwards to the rail at the furlong marker and was one paced to the wire for a minor share. TOURIST'S DREAM travelled at the back of the pack between runners at the half, was ridden for more into the far turn, began to pick up the bit in the five path at the top of the lane and was gaining slowly on runners crossing the line to be in the mix for a share in the end. HELL BENT stalked on the rail going into the first turn, settled behind runners near the rear down the back straight, showed good late energy when finally clear at the sixteenth pole and closed well late to be involved with multiple horses for the place photo at the wire. AWESOMECREST settled near the rear three wide in the beginning, rallied four wide in the second turn with three eighths to go, was in with a chance for a minor share three deep at the top of the lane and levelled out in mid stretch. KITTEN'S BOY trailed the field from the start, continued to see them all into the far turn, was urged five wide at the two furlong marker, angled out to the eight path for the drive but could not get involved late. LARAQUE broke inwards to begin, had a good spot inside tracking the top pair down the back straight, was roused to go after the loose winner three eighths from home, rallied briefly between runners at the quarter pole and emptied out in the final sixteenth. TARADAR was brushed at the start, prompted the pace into the first turn, chased the winner down the backside and through the far turn, retreated on fence in mid stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY URUS hounded the leader inside in the early going, took over to have a narrow lead on the rail turning for home, stubbornly dug in down the lane and began to get the better of her challenger in the final eighth to pull away at the wire. SIGN OF BEAUTY was reluctant to load prior to the start, broke sharp to have a slim lead down the backside, continued to engage with the winner on the far turn, bid between foes at the quarter pole and lost the battle for the top spot with a furlong remaining to finish a clear second in the end. PRINCESSONAMISSION tracked inside behind the leaders at the half, continued to never give up on the fence turning for home and determinedly finished to the wire to be a solid third crossing the line. PAINTED GLORY stalked near the back of the pack with four furlongs left to run, was roused at the quarter marker and had good late energy to finish up well in the final furlong. ATTABE was situated in midpack in the early stages of the race, three eighths from home was asked for more and offered a late finish between horses in the end. KANTBACKOFF watched the front duo contest for the front running on the turn, posed a threat in the four path at the quarter pole and yielded four wide at the furlong marker. BLUEBERRY FIELDS travelled near the back three wide between foes in the beginning, made no headway running on the turn and passed tired runners in the stretch. ADMISSIBLE settled in the middle of this large field all alone rating well on the turn, angled three wide for the run to the wire and faded in mid stretch. JANIS JOPLIN was in range of the leaders just off the fence through the turn, took closer order to the front pair at the top of the lane threatening five wide two furlongs from home and weakened in deep stretch. PROUD SPEAKER stalked near the rear down the backstretch, offered a mild turn of foot advancing on the rail early part of the turn, was in with a chance for a minor share three deep in upper stretch and stalled at the furlong pole. MORNING RUN was allowed to settle in last in the early stages, roused on the fence straightening out for the finish and made little gain running to the wire. LIAM'S AWESOME settled near the back four deep down the backside, offered little interest running throughout the turn, trailed entering the stretch drive and galloped to the finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THERE'S NO JOE took control from the onset, was relaxed on the lead setting the pace throughout the turn, was asked in mid stretch and had enough left late to hold on to a diminishing lead crossing the wire. HICKSY was pinched soon after the start, regrouped to have a good trip behind the winner through the turn, had his sights set on the winner turning for home and was gaining with each stride but could not get there in time. PROVEN STRATEGIES was bumped at the start, travelled on the rail in hand through the turn in the third flight, rallied in upper stretch on the fence and finished up to be a clear third in the end. DOWNY BOY settled on the rail in the middle of the pack on the rail running in the turn, weaved his way through the stretch and showed late gain in the three path to get up for a minor share at the finish. NIAGARA SKYLINE settled four wide outside horses close enough to the pace down the backside, was in with a chance five wide between rivals in upper stretch but could not find more late to be a threat at the finish. THE GREAT OZ sat three wide outside horses tracking in the second flight on the turn, was in range in the six path turning for home and was one paced to the wire in the final furlong. PERFECT CRIME had a stalking trip near the back, put in an early move around foes at the half, was in the mix for a share eight wide in the lane and levelled out with a furlong to go. FARAWAY KITTEN was reined in on the rail to be shuffled back in the early part of the turn, rallied two wide off the rail around horses with three furlongs to go, angled out nine deep for the drive and stalled in the final furlong. NIKOLAOU travelled on the rail near the back in the beginning, trailed this field in the ten path at the top of the stretch and offered no finish running to the line. COMMANDER JOE stalked at the back of the field in the early stages, never got involved and could not be a factor down the stretch. GRANDSON trailed the field after the start, offered little movement running on the turn and made no headway in the eighth path to the finish. BRITISH ARTILLERY pressed the issue early on, was ridden between runners to keep position three furlongs from the finish and stopped at the three sixteenth pole. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 9 6F Turf CR: 83. Optional Claiming Purse 61800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR ONTARIO SIRED ALLOWANCE WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Consider ed For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOREST BUZZ took this field down the backstretch and into the turn setting the pace, was asked at the three sixteenths marker, responded well and kept his rivals at bay in the final eighth for the victory. KINETIC STONE was nestled behind the winner on the fence throughout the turn, chased in vain the entire stretch, could not threaten and had the settle for a clear second in the end. THEBACKSTRETCHDUDE leapt up a touch at the start, rated kindly on the rail into the turn, began to pick up runners on the fence at the three furlong pole, shifted out between foes four wide at the quarter pole making a bid but could not find more to threaten the top two at the finish. RAPID TEST settled inside near the rear in the beginning stages of the race, advanced smartly on the fence through the turn, angled four wide at the top of the lane and finished up splitting foes at the sixteenth pole to get up for a small share. MENDELJOHN (IRE) prompted the pace outside on the turn, was in the three path turning for home with a chance for the win but could not find another gear and faded in the final furlong. JAMIESTA tracked three wide in between horses entering the turn, was in the mix at the quarter pole six wide and weakened in mid stretch. HIGHLAND LIFE stumbled slightly at the break, travelled in midpack down the backstretch, lost ground to competitors on the turn and was never a menace running to the finish. MIGHT BEE SPEEDY hopped at the start, stalked near the rear down the backside, could not get involved running on the turn and made little impact through the stretch to the finish line. ROLLING HILLS settled four wide not far off the pace into the turn, could not match strides with the leaders three furlongs from the prize and gave way at the top of the stretch. PUDDINGONTHERITZ was void of speed early trailing down the backstretch, could not keep up with others on the turn and lost touch with the field in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 10 1M Inner turf CR: 95. Waiver Claiming Purse 54500. INNER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).

CLAIM.OWNER: Natural Eight Stable and J & B Wright Racing Inc

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREEN FLEET tracked from inside just off the leaders, came out five wide turning for home, bid at the furlong marker, cleared and held. LAPOCHKA was reserved in the early going shifting in two to three wide early, began to receive encouragement three then four wide on the far turn, swung seven wide into upper stretch, was gaining but too late. STEAK AND CHEESE stalked early while outside foes in the second flight three to four wide, took closer order up the backstretch, launched a sweeping move to take command past the five-sixteenths, lacked the needed late kick. SALVATOR MUNDI was just a hair tight between runners after the start, raced off the pace between foes about three deep, moved out a bit on the far turn put to urging, came into upper stretch seven wide then tipped out further, ran on late to get up for fourth. DECIMATOR was lightly brushed at the start, settled mid-division racing inside saving ground, came out a bit in upper stretch, ran on evenly. UNCLE BULL broke through the gate, got away alertly and moved clear, shifted in setting the pace into the first turn, was prompted then overtaken by an outside rival and chased that one up the backstretch, retook the lead briefly early on the far turn but was overtaken leaving that bend. JACK THE CAT brushed with a rival lightly while breaking a half-step slowly, rode the rail through the first turn racing at the back, came off the fence for the far turn. CHANCEL moved forward outside the leader two to three wide to force the issue early up the backstretch, began to drop back three furlong from home and weakened. DESOLATOR was caught four wide on both turns racing mid-pack, failed to rally. FINALIST tracked up close racing off the inside, dropped back and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 7F Turf CR: 73. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 49600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS THAT HAVE RACED 3 CONSECUTIVE STARTS IN THE MAIDEN OPTIONAL $40,000 / OS CATEGORY IN 2022-23 AND DID NOT FINISH 2ND THRU 4TH. or FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENGLISH SHIRL hounded the pace under a snug hold outside in the early going, took control three deep at the quarter marker, opened up in mid stretch and held on by a diminishing margin in the end. TRILLING SONG was away slowly to begin, stalking close to the back of the pack, continued to see the field in the ten path at the top of the stretch and was full of run to the wire gaining with every stride to make it close at the finish line. WORRY LESS was squeezed at the start, was asked for some run to get a good spot tracking behind the leaders entering the turn, was ridden to go after the front pair three furlongs from home, continued to put in a game effort in the final eighth and closed between runners to be a clear third. HOLIDAY WITH AMY settled the midfield between runners in the two path with a half remaining, waited behind horses looking for room in upper stretch, finally had a clear path three wide at the sixteenth pole and got up for a minor role at the finish. MASON'S MUSIC travelled in the middle of this strung out pack three wide outside with four furlongs remaining, was in with a chance for a piece of the prize in the eight path straightening out for the run to the wire, battled with the leaders in early stretch but yielded in the final sixteenth. SIXTOFIVE settled on the rail in the middle of the pack, was ridden on the fence with three furlongs from home and could not find another gear in the late stages of the race. VELIKIY tracked three wide just off the pace outside of rivals, posed a threat in the five path turning for home and battled until the sixteenth pole giving way in deep stretch. WHISPER ME A SONG trailed the field down the backstretch, angled out to the five path entering the long stretch and showed some gumption passing weary stragglers to the finish. MERITAMEN took command from the onset, continued to dictate the pace on the turn, was collared by the winner at the top of the lane and retreated in the final eighth. TENDER SITUATION tracked on the rail behind the frontrunner in the beginning, waited patiently on the fence throughout the turn, found a seam in the four path at the three sixteenth marker but tired in the final furlong. SANDY GRACE stalked near the back on the rail in the beginning, saved all the ground through the turn and offered no finish on the fence running to the wire.
